claim.claim-text:
1. A system for separating an entrained immiscible liquid component from a wet gas stream comprising: 
a vessel having an interior in communication with a wet gas inlet, a gas outlet and a liquid outlet; 
at least one vortex tube supported within said vessel interior, the vortex tube having an inlet end and an outlet end and a tubular wall having an internal wall surface through which a gas stream passes as the gas flows between said vessel wet gas inlet and gas outlet; 
a vortex generator supported within said vortex tube intermediate said inlet and outlet ends, the vortex generator causing gas within said vortex tube to rotate to thereby cause at least some of said liquid component to be forced against said interior wall surface of said vortex tube by centrifugal action; 
a circumferentially positioned liquid outlet in said vortex tube tubular wall downstream of said vortex generator configured to strip liquid from said vortex tube interior wall along with bypass gas from said gas stream flowing through said vortex tube, stripped liquid and bypass gas entering said interior of said vessel; and 
a recycle port in said vortex tube tubular wall upstream of said vortex generator through which bypass gas flows.

13. A system for separating an entrained immiscible liquid component from a wet gas stream comprising: 
a vessel having an interior in communication with a wet gas inlet, a gas outlet and a liquid outlet; 
at least one vortex tube supported within said vessel interior, the vortex tube having an inlet end and an outlet end and a tubular wall having an internal wall surface through which a gas stream passes as the gas flows between said vessel wet gas inlet and gas outlet in said vortex tube having a recycle port in said tubular wall; 
a vortex generator supported within said vortex tube intermediate said inlet and outlet ends, the vortex generator causing gas within said vortex tube to rotate to thereby cause at least some of said liquid component to be forced against said interior wall surface of said vortex tube by centrifugal action; 
a liquid outlet in said vortex tube tubular wall downstream of said vortex generator configured to strip liquid from said vortex tube interior wall along with bypass gas from said gas stream flowing through said vortex tube, stripped liquid and bypass gas entering said interior of said vessel; and 
a venturi element positioned within said vortex tube for creating an area of pressure drop therein, said recycle port in said vortex tube having communication with said area of pressure drop by which bypass gas is drawn into said vortex tube.

24. A method for separating an entrained immiscible liquid component from a wet gas stream comprising; 
(1) passing said wet gas stream through a vortex tube having an inlet end and an outlet end and tubular wall having an internal wall surface; 
(2) causing gas within said vortex tube to rotate to thereby cause at least some of said liquid component to be forced against said interior wall surface of said vortex tube by centrifugal action; 
(3) stripping liquid from said vortex tube interior wall surface; 
(4) diverting liquid stripped from said vortex tube interior wall surface along with bypass gas out through an outlet in said vortex tube tubular wall; 
(5) recycling bypass gas back into said vortex tube; and 
(6) withdrawing for disposal liquid stripped from said vortex tube interior wall surface.
